.TH DASALL 1 "2026-05-25" "DASALL" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dasall \- installed DASALL terminal user interface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dasall
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dasall
is the installed terminal user interface for DASALL shipped by the Debian and
Ubuntu packages.

The command expects an interactive terminal. If stdin or stdout is not attached
to a TTY, it fails closed and directs the operator to
.BR dasall-cli (1)
for non-interactive control-plane tasks.

The current daemon-backed v1 operator model remains root/sudo-only. Bare
.B dasall
is the human-facing TUI entrypoint; structured control-plane operations stay on
.BR dasall-cli (1)
until a future access model explicitly changes that boundary.
.SH STARTUP NOTES
.TP
.B Interactive TTY required
The TUI requires stdin and stdout to be attached to a TTY.
.TP
.B Non-interactive control-plane
Use
.B dasall-cli
for package scripts, automation, and structured operator commands such as
.BR config ,
.BR ping ,
.BR readiness ,
.BR run ,
.BR status ,
.BR cancel ,
.BR diag ,
and
.BR knowledge .
.TP
.B Root/sudo-only daemon operator path
The installed daemon socket and packaged operator workflow remain root/sudo-only
in v1. See
.I /usr/share/doc/dasall-daemon/README.Debian
for deployment steps.
.SH PACKAGE-MODE DEPLOYMENT
For package-mode deployment, the canonical operator workflow name is still the
structured CLI:

.B sudo dasall-cli config

The canonical files remain:
.TP
.I /etc/default/dasall-daemon
Profile selection only.
.TP
.I /etc/dasall/daemon.json
Daemon override file. Only
.B daemon.*
keys are supported.

Validate a deployment configuration with:

.B . /etc/default/dasall-daemon && /usr/sbin/dasall-daemon --validate-only --profile-id="${DASALL_DAEMON_PROFILE_ID}" --config-file /etc/dasall/daemon.json
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/bin/dasall
Installed TUI command.
.TP
.I /usr/bin/dasall-cli
Installed structured control-plane command.
.TP
.I /usr/sbin/dasall-daemon
Installed daemon binary.
.TP
.I /usr/share/doc/dasall-daemon/README.Debian
Package deployment notes.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dasall-cli (1),
.BR dasall-daemon (8)